for the fire, there will be <HI>bundles</HI> of covetous per&s;ons, of drunkards, profane &s;wearers, unclean per&s;ons, formal hypocrites, unbelievers, and de&s;pi&s;ers of the go&s;pel, and the like: the &s;everal <HI>bundles</HI> being ca&s;t into hell-fire, &s;ome will burn more keenly than others, accord|ing as their &s;ins have been more heinous than the&s;e of others: a fiercer flame will &s;eize the bundles of the <HI>profane,</HI> than the bundle of <HI>un&s;anctified morali&s;ts;</HI> the furnace will be hotter to tho&s;e who &s;inned again&s;t <HI>light,</HI> than to the&s;e who lived in <HI>darkne&s;s,</HI> Luke xii. 37, 38
